237
00:18:25,428 --> 00:18:50,119
[SPEAKER_03]: partly that's supported, partly it's the changes we want to make to the job centres to make sure that where businesses and public services, the NHS doesn't go to the job centre when it's got vacancies, they should do so we want to merge those two services but the other thing if we're going to get people back into work is we have to tackle these terrible waiting lists because nearly 8 million people are on the waiting list and so it's not their fault

238
00:18:50,099 --> 00:18:52,763
[SPEAKER_03]: that they can't get back into work.

239
00:18:52,783 --> 00:18:56,128
[SPEAKER_03]: It's the fault of the government that's put us in this terrible position.

240
00:18:56,288 --> 00:18:57,710
[SPEAKER_03]: We have to address these bases.

241
00:18:57,731 --> 00:19:03,499
[SPEAKER_04]: Fundamentally, there's a very clear choice and a very clear dividing line.

242
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:07,365
[SPEAKER_04]: I think you've got to change the eligibility criteria in the welfare system.

243
00:19:08,003 --> 00:19:10,567
[SPEAKER_04]: You've got to make it clear that people who can work should work.

244
00:19:10,587 --> 00:19:28,371
[SPEAKER_04]: That means looking at all the gateways we have and actually being more rigorous about asking people to provide medical information when they're making these claims, reforming the sick note process, being stricter about saying to people who don't accept a job after 12 months that that's not OK. Those are all the practical things that I've set out.

245
00:19:28,552 --> 00:19:29,573
[SPEAKER_04]: I think that's fair.

246
00:19:29,553 --> 00:19:31,876
[SPEAKER_04]: Now, Keir Starmer can stand here tonight and say what he wants.

247
00:19:32,036 --> 00:19:36,902
[SPEAKER_04]: When I made that speech, and you can all go and read it and see what they said, they opposed every single measure.

248
00:19:37,243 --> 00:19:39,446
[SPEAKER_04]: Just two weeks ago, they were asked about it.

249
00:19:39,466 --> 00:19:41,268
[SPEAKER_04]: They said, we oppose all those measures.

250
00:19:41,589 --> 00:19:43,631
[SPEAKER_04]: So it's one thing to stand here and say all these things.

