00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:04,123
[SPEAKER_00]: Good evening, all.

285
00:22:04,163 --> 00:22:04,964
[SPEAKER_00]: We're an island.

286
00:22:05,285 --> 00:22:07,408
[SPEAKER_00]: Why can't we easily close our borders?

287
00:22:08,711 --> 00:22:10,414
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you, Steve, for that question.

288
00:22:10,674 --> 00:22:11,736
[SPEAKER_10]: Keir Starmer.

289
00:22:11,756 --> 00:22:19,369
[SPEAKER_03]: Steve, the biggest threat to our borders at the moment is the very many people arriving by small boat over the Channel.

290
00:22:20,031 --> 00:22:21,754
[SPEAKER_03]: And there are record numbers.

291
00:22:21,994 --> 00:22:27,604
[SPEAKER_03]: Since Rishi Sunak became Prime Minister, 50,000 people have come across by small boat.

292
00:22:27,584 --> 00:22:31,008
[SPEAKER_03]: and the government has effectively lost control of our borders.

293
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:40,059
[SPEAKER_03]: And that means it's not just a border security issue, it's actually a national security issue, because the government's lost control of who's coming and what their background is.

294
00:22:40,399 --> 00:22:45,325
[SPEAKER_03]: Now, I think that nobody but nobody should be making that journey across the Channel.

295
00:22:45,706 --> 00:22:49,330
[SPEAKER_03]: And we have to smash the gangs that are running this vile trade.

296
00:22:49,630 --> 00:22:55,397
[SPEAKER_03]: There are gangs that are making a fortune putting people into boats across the Channel, an absolute fortune.

297
00:22:55,377 --> 00:22:57,020
[SPEAKER_03]: and I think they can be taken down.

298
00:22:57,281 --> 00:23:11,310
[SPEAKER_03]: And Steve, before I was a politician, I was the chief prosecutor for England and Wales, so I ran all criminal prosecutions in England and Wales, in all of our criminal courts, and we had to deal with terrorist plots and other plots, drug plots,

299
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:15,034
[SPEAKER_03]: and gun plots, which were across various other countries.

300
00:23:15,295 --> 00:23:20,841
[SPEAKER_03]: We grouped together with police and law enforcement across Europe, and we took down those terrorist gangs.

301
00:23:21,302 --> 00:23:22,083
[SPEAKER_03]: I've seen it done.

302
00:23:22,103 --> 00:23:24,446
[SPEAKER_03]: I've been part of the operations to do it.

303
00:23:24,526 --> 00:23:31,574
[SPEAKER_03]: I do not accept, I will never accept, that the only gangs that apparently can't be taken down are the gangs that are putting vulnerable people in boats to go across the Channel.

304
00:23:31,594 --> 00:23:38,783
[SPEAKER_10]: Let's turn to Rishi Sunak, because we haven't heard from him yet on Steve's question, which was, we're an island, why can't we easily close our borders?

305
00:23:38,898 --> 00:23:40,541
[SPEAKER_04]: Steve, you're right to highlight the issue.

306
00:23:40,581 --> 00:23:42,444
[SPEAKER_04]: It's completely unfair what's happening.

307
00:23:42,465 --> 00:23:52,523
[SPEAKER_04]: When people come here illegally, jump the queue, it not only puts pressure on public services and not only threatens our security, it's an affront to that sense of fairness, which is fundamental to our national character.

308
00:23:52,783 --> 00:23:55,148
[SPEAKER_04]: And that's why I've made it a priority to stop the boats.

309
00:23:55,348 --> 00:23:56,230
[SPEAKER_04]: We have made progress.

310
00:23:56,590 --> 00:24:00,197
[SPEAKER_04]: The numbers have come down over the past 12 months compared to the 12 months before.

311
00:24:00,177 --> 00:24:04,001
[SPEAKER_04]: But, in order to fully solve this problem, you need a deterrent.

312
00:24:04,021 --> 00:24:09,668
[SPEAKER_04]: We need to make it crystal clear to people that if they come to our country illegally, they won't be able to stay.

313
00:24:09,688 --> 00:24:20,840
[SPEAKER_04]: And that's why, if I'm your Prime Minister on July 5th, the flights will go to Rwanda, we will build that deterrent that multiple other European countries now agree is the right way to deal with this problem, and that's how we solve this problem.

314
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:25,485
[SPEAKER_04]: If Keir Starmer is your Prime Minister, all those illegal migrants will be out on our streets.

315
00:24:25,666 --> 00:24:26,827
[SPEAKER_04]: And that is the choice for you.

316
00:24:26,887 --> 00:24:29,610
[SPEAKER_04]: Do not surrender our borders to the Labour Party.

317
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:34,560
